AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The place(s) from which the offer can be obtained (e.g. store locations).

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The away team in a sports event.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of object. The person or organization being followed.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-14 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: gtin14

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The GTIN-8 code of the product, or the product to which the offer refers. This code is also known as EAN/UCC-8 or 8-digit EAN. See GS1 GTIN Summary for more details.
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: gtin8

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates a CreativeWork that is (in some sense) a part of this CreativeWork.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A contact location for a person's residence.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The home team in a sports event.

See background notes for more details.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An image of the item. This can be a URL or a fully described ImageObject.
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: image

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A single ingredient used in the recipe, e.g. sugar, flour or garlic.
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: ingredients

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The ISBN of the book.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of instrument. The language used on this action.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An organization identifier that uniquely identifies a legal entity as defined in ISO 17442.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of participant. The person that lends the object being borrowed.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The location of for example where the event is happening, an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Indicates the primary entity described in some page or other CreativeWork.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A material that something is made from, e.g. leather, wool, cotton, paper.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: memberOf

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The object upon which the action is carried out, whose state is kept intact or changed. Also known as the semantic roles patient, affected or undergoer (which change their state) or theme (which doesn't). e.g. John read a book.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of participant. The opponent on this action.
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: opponent

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: partOfSeries

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The TV series to which this episode or season belongs.
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: partOfTVSeries

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: Other co-agents that participated in the action indirectly. e.g. John wrote a book with Steve.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The length of time it takes to perform instructions or a direction (not including time to prepare the supplies), in ISO 8601 duration format.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A photograph of this place.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The position of an item in a series or sequence of items.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The product identifier, such as ISBN. For example: meta itemprop="productID" content="isbn:123-456-789".

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The quantity produced by the recipe (for example, number of people served, number of servings, etc).
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: recipeYield

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of participant. The participant who is at the receiving end of the action.
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: recipient

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of object. The object that is being replaced.
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: replacee

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: A sub property of object. The object that replaces.
AnnotationProperty.rdfs:label: replacer

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The result produced in the action. e.g. John wrote a book.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: 'vendor' is an earlier term for 'seller'.

AnnotationProperty.rdfs:comment: The movie presented during this event.

Class.rdfs:comment:
A BreadcrumbList is an ItemList consisting of a chain of linked Web pages, typically described using at least their URL and their name, and typically ending with the current page.

The position property is used to reconstruct the order of the items in a BreadcrumbList The convention is that a breadcrumb list has an itemListOrder of ItemListOrderAscending (lower values listed first), and that the first items in this list correspond to the "top" or beginning of the breadcrumb trail, e.g. with a site or section homepage. The specific values of 'position' are not assigned meaning for a BreadcrumbList, but they should be integers, e.g. beginning with '1' for the first item in the list.

Class.rdfs:comment:
A CreativeWorkSeries in schema.org is a group of related items, typically but not necessarily of the same kind. CreativeWorkSeries are usually organized into some order, often chronological. Unlike ItemList which is a general purpose data structure for lists of things, the emphasis with CreativeWorkSeries is on published materials (written e.g. books and periodicals, or media such as tv, radio and games).

Specific subtypes are available for describing TVSeries, RadioSeries, MovieSeries, BookSeries, Periodical and VideoGameSeries. In each case, the hasPart / isPartOf properties can be used to relate the CreativeWorkSeries to its parts. The general CreativeWorkSeries type serves largely just to organize these more specific and practical subtypes.

It is common for properties applicable to an item from the series to be usefully applied to the containing group. Schema.org attempts to anticipate some of these cases, but publishers should be free to apply properties of the series parts to the series as a whole wherever they seem appropriate.

A hotel is an establishment that provides lodging paid on a short-term basis (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.
Class.rdfs:label: Hotel

Class.rdfs:comment:
A hotel room is a single room in a hotel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.
Class.rdfs:label: HotelRoom

Class.rdfs:comment: A house is a building or structure that has the ability to be occupied for habitation by humans or other creatures (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/House).
Class.rdfs:label: House

Class.rdfs:comment: A house painting service.
Class.rdfs:label: HousePainter

Class.rdfs:comment: Instructions that explain how to achieve a result by performing a sequence of steps.
Class.rdfs:label: HowTo

Class.rdfs:comment: A direction indicating a single action to do in the instructions for how to achieve a result.
Class.rdfs:label: HowToDirection

Class.rdfs:comment: An item used as either a tool or supply when performing the instructions for how to to achieve a result.
Class.rdfs:label: HowToItem

Class.rdfs:comment: A sub-grouping of steps in the instructions for how to achieve a result (e.g. steps for making a pie crust within a pie recipe).
Class.rdfs:label: HowToSection

Class.rdfs:comment: A step in the instructions for how to achieve a result. It is an ordered list with HowToDirection and/or HowToTip items.
Class.rdfs:label: HowToStep

Class.rdfs:comment: A supply consumed when performing the instructions for how to achieve a result.
Class.rdfs:label: HowToSupply

Class.rdfs:comment: An explanation in the instructions for how to achieve a result. It provides supplementary information about a technique, supply, author's preference, etc. It can explain what could be done, or what should not be done, but doesn't specify what should be done (see HowToDirection).
Class.rdfs:label: HowToTip

Class.rdfs:comment: A tool used (but not consumed) when performing instructions for how to achieve a result.
Class.rdfs:label: HowToTool

Class.rdfs:comment: An ice cream shop.
Class.rdfs:label: IceCreamShop

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of intentionally disregarding the object. An agent ignores an object.
Class.rdfs:label: IgnoreAction

Class.rdfs:comment: Web page type: Image gallery page.
Class.rdfs:label: ImageGallery

Class.rdfs:comment: An image file.
Class.rdfs:label: ImageObject

Class.rdfs:comment: A single, identifiable product instance (e.g. a laptop with a particular serial number).
Class.rdfs:label: IndividualProduct

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of notifying someone of information pertinent to them, with no expectation of a response.
Class.rdfs:label: InformAction

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of adding at a specific location in an ordered collection.
Class.rdfs:label: InsertAction

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of installing an application.
Class.rdfs:label: InstallAction

Class.rdfs:comment: An Insurance agency.
Class.rdfs:label: InsuranceAgency

Class.rdfs:comment: A utility class that serves as the umbrella for a number of 'intangible' things such as quantities, structured values, etc.
Class.rdfs:label: Intangible

Class.rdfs:comment: Data type: Integer.
Class.rdfs:label: Integer

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of interacting with another person or organization.
Class.rdfs:label: InteractAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A summary of how users have interacted with this CreativeWork. In most cases, authors will use a subtype to specify the specific type of interaction.
Class.rdfs:label: InteractionCounter

Class.rdfs:comment: An internet cafe.
Class.rdfs:label: InternetCafe

Class.rdfs:comment: A type of financial product that typically requires the client to transfer funds to a financial service in return for potential beneficial financial return.
Class.rdfs:label: InvestmentOrDeposit

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of asking someone to attend an event. Reciprocal of RsvpAction.
Class.rdfs:label: InviteAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A statement of the money due for goods or services; a bill.
Class.rdfs:label: Invoice

Class.rdfs:comment: A list of possible product availability options.
Class.rdfs:label: ItemAvailability

Class.rdfs:comment: A list of items of any sort—for example, Top 10 Movies About Weathermen, or Top 100 Party Songs. Not to be confused with HTML lists, which are often used only for formatting.
Class.rdfs:label: ItemList

Class.rdfs:comment: Enumerated for values for itemListOrder for indicating how an ordered ItemList is organized.
Class.rdfs:label: ItemListOrderType

Class.rdfs:comment: A page devoted to a single item, such as a particular product or hotel.
Class.rdfs:label: ItemPage

Class.rdfs:comment: A jewelry store.
Class.rdfs:label: JewelryStore

Class.rdfs:comment: A listing that describes a job opening in a certain organization.
Class.rdfs:label: JobPosting

Class.rdfs:comment:
An agent joins an event/group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

  • RegisterAction: Unlike RegisterAction, JoinAction refers to joining a group/team of people.
  • SubscribeAction: Unlike SubscribeAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be receiving updates.
  • FollowAction: Unlike FollowAction, JoinAction does not imply that you'll be polling for updates.
Class.rdfs:label: JoinAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A lake (for example, Lake Pontrachain).
Class.rdfs:label: LakeBodyOfWater

Class.rdfs:comment: A landform or physical feature. Landform elements include mountains, plains, lakes, rivers, seascape and oceanic waterbody interface features such as bays, peninsulas, seas and so forth, including sub-aqueous terrain features such as submersed mountain ranges, volcanoes, and the great ocean basins.
Class.rdfs:label: Landform

Class.rdfs:comment: An historical landmark or building.
Class.rdfs:label: LandmarksOrHistoricalBuildings

Class.rdfs:comment: Natural languages such as Spanish, Tamil, Hindi, English, etc. Formal language code tags expressed in BCP 47 can be used via the alternateName property. The Language type previously also covered programming languages such as Scheme and Lisp, which are now best represented using ComputerLanguage.
Class.rdfs:label: Language

Class.rdfs:comment:
An agent leaves an event / group with participants/friends at a location.

Related actions:

  • JoinAction: The antonym of LeaveAction.
  • UnRegisterAction: Unlike UnRegisterAction, LeaveAction implies leaving a group/team of people rather than a service.
Class.rdfs:label: LeaveAction

Class.rdfs:comment:
A LegalService is a business that provides legally-oriented services, advice and representation, e.g. law firms.

As a LocalBusiness it can be described as a provider of one or more Service(s).
Class.rdfs:label: LegalService

Class.rdfs:comment: A legislative building—for example, the state capitol.
Class.rdfs:label: LegislativeBuilding

Class.rdfs:comment:
The act of providing an object under an agreement that it will be returned at a later date. Reciprocal of BorrowAction.

Related actions:

  • BorrowAction: Reciprocal of LendAction.
Class.rdfs:label: LendAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A library.
Class.rdfs:label: Library

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of expressing a positive sentiment about the object. An agent likes an object (a proposition, topic or theme) with participants.
Class.rdfs:label: LikeAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A shop that sells alcoholic drinks such as wine, beer, whisky and other spirits.
Class.rdfs:label: LiquorStore

Class.rdfs:comment: An list item, e.g. a step in a checklist or how-to description.
Class.rdfs:label: ListItem

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of consuming audio content.
Class.rdfs:label: ListenAction

Class.rdfs:comment: Event type: Literary event.
Class.rdfs:label: LiteraryEvent

Class.rdfs:comment: A blog post intended to provide a rolling textual coverage of an ongoing event through continuous updates.
Class.rdfs:label: LiveBlogPosting

Class.rdfs:comment: A financial product for the loaning of an amount of money under agreed terms and charges.
Class.rdfs:label: LoanOrCredit

Class.rdfs:comment: A particular physical business or branch of an organization. Examples of LocalBusiness include a restaurant, a particular branch of a restaurant chain, a branch of a bank, a medical practice, a club, a bowling alley, etc.
Class.rdfs:label: LocalBusiness

Class.rdfs:comment: Specifies a location feature by providing a structured value representing a feature of an accommodation as a property-value pair of varying degrees of formality.
Class.rdfs:label: LocationFeatureSpecification

Class.rdfs:comment: A DeliveryMethod in which an item is made available via locker.
Class.rdfs:label: LockerDelivery

Class.rdfs:comment: A locksmith.
Class.rdfs:label: Locksmith

Class.rdfs:comment: A lodging business, such as a motel, hotel, or inn.
Class.rdfs:label: LodgingBusiness

Class.rdfs:comment:
A reservation for lodging at a hotel, motel, inn, etc.

Note: This type is for information about actual reservations, e.g. in confirmation emails or HTML pages with individual confirmations of reservations.
Class.rdfs:label: LodgingReservation

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of being defeated in a competitive activity.
Class.rdfs:label: LoseAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A map.
Class.rdfs:label: Map

Class.rdfs:comment: An enumeration of several kinds of Map.
Class.rdfs:label: MapCategoryType

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of marrying a person.
Class.rdfs:label: MarryAction

Class.rdfs:comment: Properties that take Mass as values are of the form '<Number> <Mass unit of measure>'. E.g., '7 kg'.
Class.rdfs:label: Mass

Class.rdfs:comment: A media object, such as an image, video, or audio object embedded in a web page or a downloadable dataset i.e. DataDownload. Note that a creative work may have many media objects associated with it on the same web page. For example, a page about a single song (MusicRecording) may have a music video (VideoObject), and a high and low bandwidth audio stream (2 AudioObject's).
Class.rdfs:label: MediaObject

Class.rdfs:comment: A medical organization (physical or not), such as hospital, institution or clinic.
Class.rdfs:label: MedicalOrganization

Class.rdfs:comment:
A meeting room, conference room, or conference hall is a room provided for singular events such as business conferences and meetings (Source: Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia, see http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_hall).

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.
Class.rdfs:label: MeetingRoom

Class.rdfs:comment: A men's clothing store.
Class.rdfs:label: MensClothingStore

Class.rdfs:comment: A structured representation of food or drink items available from a FoodEstablishment.
Class.rdfs:label: Menu

Class.rdfs:comment: A food or drink item listed in a menu or menu section.
Class.rdfs:label: MenuItem

Class.rdfs:comment: A sub-grouping of food or drink items in a menu. E.g. courses (such as 'Dinner', 'Breakfast', etc.), specific type of dishes (such as 'Meat', 'Vegan', 'Drinks', etc.), or some other classification made by the menu provider.
Class.rdfs:label: MenuSection

Class.rdfs:comment: A single message from a sender to one or more organizations or people.
Class.rdfs:label: Message

Class.rdfs:comment: A middle school (typically for children aged around 11-14, although this varies somewhat).
Class.rdfs:label: MiddleSchool

Class.rdfs:comment: A software application designed specifically to work well on a mobile device such as a telephone.
Class.rdfs:label: MobileApplication

Class.rdfs:comment: A store that sells mobile phones and related accessories.
Class.rdfs:label: MobilePhoneStore

Class.rdfs:comment: A monetary value or range. This type can be used to describe an amount of money such as $50 USD, or a range as in describing a bank account being suitable for a balance between £1,000 and £1,000,000 GBP, or the value of a salary, etc. It is recommended to use PriceSpecification Types to describe the price of an Offer, Invoice, etc.
Class.rdfs:label: MonetaryAmount

Class.rdfs:comment: A mosque.
Class.rdfs:label: Mosque

Class.rdfs:comment:
A motel.

See also the dedicated document on the use of schema.org for marking up hotels and other forms of accommodations.
Class.rdfs:label: Motel

Class.rdfs:comment: A motorcycle dealer.
Class.rdfs:label: MotorcycleDealer

Class.rdfs:comment: A motorcycle repair shop.
Class.rdfs:label: MotorcycleRepair

Class.rdfs:comment: A mountain, like Mount Whitney or Mount Everest.
Class.rdfs:label: Mountain

Class.rdfs:comment:
The act of an agent relocating to a place.

Related actions:

  • TransferAction: Unlike TransferAction, the subject of the move is a living Person or Organization rather than an inanimate object.
Class.rdfs:label: MoveAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A movie.
Class.rdfs:label: Movie

Class.rdfs:comment: A short segment/part of a movie.
Class.rdfs:label: MovieClip

Class.rdfs:comment: A movie rental store.
Class.rdfs:label: MovieRentalStore

Class.rdfs:comment: A series of movies. Included movies can be indicated with the hasPart property.
Class.rdfs:label: MovieSeries

Class.rdfs:comment: A movie theater.
Class.rdfs:label: MovieTheater

Class.rdfs:comment: A moving company.
Class.rdfs:label: MovingCompany

Class.rdfs:comment: A museum.
Class.rdfs:label: Museum

Class.rdfs:comment: A collection of music tracks.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicAlbum

Class.rdfs:comment: Classification of the album by it's type of content: soundtrack, live album, studio album, etc.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicAlbumProductionType

Class.rdfs:comment: The kind of release which this album is: single, EP or album.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicAlbumReleaseType

Class.rdfs:comment: A musical composition.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicComposition

Class.rdfs:comment: Event type: Music event.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicEvent

Class.rdfs:comment: A musical group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a choir. Can also be a solo musician.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicGroup

Class.rdfs:comment: A collection of music tracks in playlist form.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicPlaylist

Class.rdfs:comment: A music recording (track), usually a single song.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicRecording

Class.rdfs:comment: A MusicRelease is a specific release of a music album.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicRelease

Class.rdfs:comment: Format of this release (the type of recording media used, ie. compact disc, digital media, LP, etc.).
Class.rdfs:label: MusicReleaseFormatType

Class.rdfs:comment: A music store.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicStore

Class.rdfs:comment: A music venue.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicVenue

Class.rdfs:comment: A music video file.
Class.rdfs:label: MusicVideoObject

Class.rdfs:comment: Organization: Non-governmental Organization.
Class.rdfs:label: NGO

Class.rdfs:comment: A nail salon.
Class.rdfs:label: NailSalon

Class.rdfs:comment:
A NewsArticle is an article whose content reports news, or provides background context and supporting materials for understanding the news.

A more detailed overview of schema.org News markup is also available.
Class.rdfs:label: NewsArticle

Class.rdfs:comment: A nightclub or discotheque.
Class.rdfs:label: NightClub

Class.rdfs:comment: A notary.
Class.rdfs:label: Notary

Class.rdfs:comment: A file containing a note, primarily for the author.
Class.rdfs:label: NoteDigitalDocument

Class.rdfs:comment: Nutritional information about the recipe.
Class.rdfs:label: NutritionInformation

Class.rdfs:comment: An ocean (for example, the Pacific).
Class.rdfs:label: OceanBodyOfWater

Class.rdfs:comment:
An offer to transfer some rights to an item or to provide a service — for example, an offer to sell tickets to an event, to rent the DVD of a movie, to stream a TV show over the internet, to repair a motorcycle, or to loan a book.

For GTIN-related fields, see Check Digit calculator and validation guide from GS1.
Class.rdfs:label: Offer

Class.rdfs:comment: An OfferCatalog is an ItemList that contains related Offers and/or further OfferCatalogs that are offeredBy the same provider.
Class.rdfs:label: OfferCatalog

Class.rdfs:comment: A list of possible conditions for the item.
Class.rdfs:label: OfferItemCondition

Class.rdfs:comment: An office equipment store.
Class.rdfs:label: OfficeEquipmentStore

Class.rdfs:comment: A publication event e.g. catch-up TV or radio podcast, during which a program is available on-demand.
Class.rdfs:label: OnDemandEvent

Class.rdfs:comment:
A structured value providing information about the opening hours of a place or a certain service inside a place.

The place is open if the opens property is specified, and closed otherwise.

If the value for the closes property is less than the value for the opens property then the hour range is assumed to span over the next day.
Class.rdfs:label: OpeningHoursSpecification

Class.rdfs:comment: An order is a confirmation of a transaction (a receipt), which can contain multiple line items, each represented by an Offer that has been accepted by the customer.
Class.rdfs:label: Order

Class.rdfs:comment: An agent orders an object/product/service to be delivered/sent.
Class.rdfs:label: OrderAction

Class.rdfs:comment: An order item is a line of an order. It includes the quantity and shipping details of a bought offer.
Class.rdfs:label: OrderItem

Class.rdfs:comment: Enumerated status values for Order.
Class.rdfs:label: OrderStatus

Class.rdfs:comment: An organization such as a school, NGO, corporation, club, etc.
Class.rdfs:label: Organization

Class.rdfs:comment: A subclass of Role used to describe roles within organizations.
Class.rdfs:label: OrganizationRole

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of manipulating/administering/supervising/controlling one or more objects.
Class.rdfs:label: OrganizeAction

Class.rdfs:comment: An outlet store.
Class.rdfs:label: OutletStore

Class.rdfs:comment: A structured value providing information about when a certain organization or person owned a certain product.
Class.rdfs:label: OwnershipInfo

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of producing a painting, typically with paint and canvas as instruments.
Class.rdfs:label: PaintAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A painting.
Class.rdfs:label: Painting

Class.rdfs:comment: The delivery of a parcel either via the postal service or a commercial service.
Class.rdfs:label: ParcelDelivery

Class.rdfs:comment:
A private parcel service as the delivery mode available for a certain offer.

Commonly used values:

  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DHL
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#FederalExpress
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#UPS
Class.rdfs:label: ParcelService

Class.rdfs:comment: A set of characteristics describing parents, who can be interested in viewing some content.
Class.rdfs:label: ParentAudience

Class.rdfs:comment: A park.
Class.rdfs:label: Park

Class.rdfs:comment: A parking lot or other parking facility.
Class.rdfs:label: ParkingFacility

Class.rdfs:comment: A shop that will buy, or lend money against the security of, personal possessions.
Class.rdfs:label: PawnShop

Class.rdfs:comment: An agent pays a price to a participant.
Class.rdfs:label: PayAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A payment method using a credit, debit, store or other card to associate the payment with an account.
Class.rdfs:label: PaymentCard

Class.rdfs:comment: The costs of settling the payment using a particular payment method.
Class.rdfs:label: PaymentChargeSpecification

Class.rdfs:comment:
A payment method is a standardized procedure for transferring the monetary amount for a purchase. Payment methods are characterized by the legal and technical structures used, and by the organization or group carrying out the transaction.

Commonly used values:

  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByBankTransferInAdvance
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#ByInvoice
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#Cash
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#CheckInAdvance
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#COD
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#DirectDebit
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#GoogleCheckout
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PayPal
  • http://purl.org/goodrelations/v1#PaySwarm
Class.rdfs:label: PaymentMethod

Class.rdfs:comment: A Service to transfer funds from a person or organization to a beneficiary person or organization.
Class.rdfs:label: PaymentService

Class.rdfs:comment: A specific payment status. For example, PaymentDue, PaymentComplete, etc.
Class.rdfs:label: PaymentStatusType

Class.rdfs:comment: A set of characteristics belonging to people, e.g. who compose an item's target audience.
Class.rdfs:label: PeopleAudience

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of participating in performance arts.
Class.rdfs:label: PerformAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A PerformanceRole is a Role that some entity places with regard to a theatrical performance, e.g. in a Movie, TVSeries etc.
Class.rdfs:label: PerformanceRole

Class.rdfs:comment: A theater or other performing art center.
Class.rdfs:label: PerformingArtsTheater

Class.rdfs:comment: A performance group, such as a band, an orchestra, or a circus.
Class.rdfs:label: PerformingGroup

Class.rdfs:comment:
A publication in any medium issued in successive parts bearing numerical or chronological designations and intended, such as a magazine, scholarly journal, or newspaper to continue indefinitely.

See also blog post.
Class.rdfs:label: Periodical

Class.rdfs:comment: A permit issued by an organization, e.g. a parking pass.
Class.rdfs:label: Permit

Class.rdfs:comment: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).
Class.rdfs:label: Person

Class.rdfs:comment: A pet store.
Class.rdfs:label: PetStore

Class.rdfs:comment: A pharmacy or drugstore.
Class.rdfs:label: Pharmacy

Class.rdfs:comment: A photograph.
Class.rdfs:label: Photograph

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of capturing still images of objects using a camera.
Class.rdfs:label: PhotographAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A doctor's office.
Class.rdfs:label: Physician

Class.rdfs:comment: Entities that have a somewhat fixed, physical extension.
Class.rdfs:label: Place

Class.rdfs:comment: Place of worship, such as a church, synagogue, or mosque.
Class.rdfs:label: PlaceOfWorship

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of planning the execution of an event/task/action/reservation/plan to a future date.
Class.rdfs:label: PlanAction

Class.rdfs:comment:
The act of playing/exercising/training/performing for enjoyment, leisure, recreation, Competition or exercise.

Related actions:

  • ListenAction: Unlike ListenAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to performing for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming music.
  • WatchAction: Unlike WatchAction (which is under ConsumeAction), PlayAction refers to showing/displaying for an audience or at an event, rather than consuming visual content.
Class.rdfs:label: PlayAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A playground.
Class.rdfs:label: Playground

Class.rdfs:comment: A plumbing service.
Class.rdfs:label: Plumber

Class.rdfs:comment: A police station.
Class.rdfs:label: PoliceStation

Class.rdfs:comment: A pond.
Class.rdfs:label: Pond

Class.rdfs:comment: A post office.
Class.rdfs:label: PostOffice

Class.rdfs:comment: The mailing address.
Class.rdfs:label: PostalAddress

Class.rdfs:comment: The act of inserting at the beginning if an ordered collection.
Class.rdfs:label: PrependAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A preschool.
Class.rdfs:label: Preschool

Class.rdfs:comment: A file containing slides or used for a presentation.
Class.rdfs:label: PresentationDigitalDocument

Class.rdfs:comment: A structured value representing a price or price range. Typically, only the subclasses of this type are used for markup. It is recommended to use MonetaryAmount to describe independent amounts of money such as a salary, credit card limits, etc.
Class.rdfs:label: PriceSpecification

Class.rdfs:comment: Any offered product or service. For example: a pair of shoes; a concert ticket; the rental of a car; a haircut; or an episode of a TV show streamed online.
Class.rdfs:label: Product

Class.rdfs:comment: A datasheet or vendor specification of a product (in the sense of a prototypical description).
Class.rdfs:label: ProductModel

Class.rdfs:comment:
Original definition: "provider of professional services."

The general ProfessionalService type for local businesses was deprecated due to confusion with Service. For reference, the types that it included were: Dentist, AccountingService, Attorney, Notary, as well as types for several kinds of HomeAndConstructionBusiness: Electrician, GeneralContractor, HousePainter, Locksmith, Plumber, RoofingContractor. LegalService was introduced as a more inclusive supertype of Attorney.
Class.rdfs:label: ProfessionalService

Class.rdfs:comment: Web page type: Profile page.
Class.rdfs:label: ProfilePage

Class.rdfs:comment: Used to describe membership in a loyalty programs (e.g. "StarAliance"), traveler clubs (e.g. "AAA"), purchase clubs ("Safeway Club"), etc.
Class.rdfs:label: ProgramMembership

Class.rdfs:comment:
A property-value pair, e.g. representing a feature of a product or place. Use the 'name' property for the name of the property. If there is an additional human-readable version of the value, put that into the 'description' property.

Always use specific schema.org properties when a) they exist and b) you can populate them. Using PropertyValue as a substitute will typically not trigger the same effect as using the original, specific property.
Class.rdfs:label: PropertyValue

Class.rdfs:comment: A Property value specification.
Class.rdfs:label: PropertyValueSpecification

Class.rdfs:comment: A public swimming pool.
Class.rdfs:label: PublicSwimmingPool

Class.rdfs:comment: A PublicationEvent corresponds indifferently to the event of publication for a CreativeWork of any type e.g. a broadcast event, an on-demand event, a book/journal publication via a variety of delivery media.
Class.rdfs:label: PublicationEvent

Class.rdfs:comment:
A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or publication volume, often numbered, usually containing a grouping of works such as articles.

blog post.
Class.rdfs:label: PublicationIssue

Class.rdfs:comment:
A part of a successively published publication such as a periodical or multi-volume work, often numbered. It may represent a time span, such as a year.

  <br/><br/>See also <a href="http://blog.schema.org/2014/09/schemaorg-support-for-bibliographic_2.html">blog post</a>.
Class.rdfs:label: PublicationVolume

Class.rdfs:comment: A QAPage is a WebPage focussed on a specific Question and its Answer(s), e.g. in a question answering site or documenting Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs).
Class.rdfs:label: QAPage

Class.rdfs:comment: A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the power cord plug type 'US' or the garment sizes 'S', 'M', 'L', and 'XL'.
Class.rdfs:label: QualitativeValue

Class.rdfs:comment: A point value or interval for product characteristics and other purposes.
Class.rdfs:label: QuantitativeValue

Class.rdfs:comment: Quantities such as distance, time, mass, weight, etc. Particular instances of say Mass are entities like '3 Kg' or '4 milligrams'.
Class.rdfs:label: Quantity

Class.rdfs:comment: A specific question - e.g. from a user seeking answers online, or collected in a Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ) document.
Class.rdfs:label: Question

Class.rdfs:comment: An agent quotes/estimates/appraises an object/product/service with a price at a location/store.
Class.rdfs:label: QuoteAction

Class.rdfs:comment: A place offering space for "Recreational Vehicles", Caravans, mobile homes and the like.
Class.rdfs:label: RVPark

Class.rdfs:comment: A unique instance of a radio BroadcastService on a CableOrSatelliteService lineup.
Class.rdfs:label: RadioChannel

Class.rdfs:comment: A short radio program or a segment/part of a radio program.
Class.rdfs:label: RadioClip

Class.rdfs:comment: A radio episode which can be part of a series or season.
Class.rdfs:label: RadioEpisode

Class.rdfs:comment: Season dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.
Class.rdfs:label: RadioSeason

Class.rdfs:comment: CreativeWorkSeries dedicated to radio broadcast and associated online delivery.
Class.rdfs:label: RadioSeries

Class.rdfs:comment: A radio station.
Class.rdfs:label: RadioStation

  • Times are specified using 24:00 time. For example, 3pm is specified as 15:00.
  • Here is an example: <time itemprop="openingHours" datetime="Tu,Th 16:00-20:00">Tuesdays and Thursdays 4-8pm</time>.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment:
The offer price of a product, or of a price component when attached to PriceSpecification and its subtypes.

Usage guidelines:

  • Use the priceCurrency property (with ISO 4217 codes e.g. "USD") instead of including ambiguous symbols such as '$' in the value.
  • Use '.' (Unicode 'FULL STOP' (U+002E)) rather than ',' to indicate a decimal point. Avoid using these symbols as a readability separator.
  • Note that both RDFa and Microdata syntax allow the use of a "content=" attribute for publishing simple machine-readable values alongside more human-friendly formatting.
  • Use values from 0123456789 (Unicode 'DIGIT ZERO' (U+0030) to 'DIGIT NINE' (U+0039)) rather than superficially similiar Unicode symbols.
